node.text:
Now that the new year is here I feel it’s important to share this with you so can all be aware of the abuse that these beautiful animals go through so people can take some cute photos during their vacation. .
hope this Video🎥 can open Your eyes👀 a bit and give you a perspective on "Animal Interaction“ you might never had before!🤷🏼‍♂️ It‘s all up to US (Humans) if we accept things like this or not! If we support these things or not! 😓
•
Please SHARE this Video and help us shine a light on this serious global🌍 problem‼️Together we CAN END Animal Cruelty & Slavery🐾⛓
•
Also tag at least 3 Friends in the comments so we can spread this message. .
.
Thank you @dean.schneider for all the work you’re doing!

node.text:
Curious dog 🐶 watching dolphin swim upfront then boat. Dolphins are extremely curious and intelligent animals. When they notice an unfamiliar object moving along the surface of the water their inquisitive nature compels them to approach ships and determine the cause of the commotion.

🎥 @dylan.dehaas
📍 Perth, Australia

node.text:
Enter the overgrown tunnel of plants into Montrose’s Lost Books in Los Angeles, CA. There’s no sign. No phone number. No website. But if you venture in through the Instagram-ready tunnel of plants and greenery, you’ll emerge into the world of Lost Books.

Located in Montrose in northeast Los Angeles County, the shop, which opened quietly in late June, is a sister to downtown L.A.’s Last Bookstore, the massive store and tourist spot known for its huge inventory and its own picture-perfect archway and book-related sculptures and photo spots.

🎥 @yukokitchen 
📍@lostbooksla LA, CA USA

node.text:
Meet Simon @backpackingkitty one of the most well traveled cats in the world! Him and @jjyosh travel the world in style! Simon’s been to over 100 destinations, and has climbed the highest peaks in the the USA. He’s not afraid of getting wet and dirty to explore rivers and nature. JJ shared with with our team that they enjoying dining together and their  favorite dish is Shrimp 😊- This has to be one of the most awesome travel duo’s on social media.

🎥 @jjyosh & @backpackingkitty 
📍 🌎

This is why you should spend a summer in Provence, France 🇫🇷 .  Provence, a region in southeastern France bordering Italy and the Mediterranean Sea, is known for its diverse landscapes, from the Southern Alps and Camargue plains to rolling vineyards, olive groves, pine forests and lavender fields. To the south is the Côte d'Azur (or French Riviera), where the elegant city of Nice and glamorous resort towns such as Saint-Tropez and Cannes line the coast.

🎥 @samanthavarvel 
📍Provence, France 🇫🇷

node.text:
If you’re scared of heights then you might want to look away now, because this walkway in China is your worst nightmare come true. The fact that it’s attached 4,600ft (1,403 metres) up the side of a mountain is scary enough, but the fact that it’s also made of glass is nothing short of terrifying.

Situated on the side of Tianmen mountain in Zhangjiajie National Forest Park, Hunan Province, the walkway is 328ft (100 metres) long and 5.2ft (1.6 metres) wide. It’s known as the Coiling Dragon Cliff skywalk, and as you can see, it certainly isn’t for the faint-hearted, but anybody who finds the courage to brave the walkway will be rewarded with an utterly breathtaking view that few will ever experience. (via bored panda) 

🎥 TikTok user GreySwan123 
📍 China 🇨🇳

node.text:
Have you experienced bioluminescence  in person? Bioluminescence occurs through a chemical reaction that produces light energy within an organism's body. For a reaction to occur, a species must contain luciferin, a molecule that, when it reacts with oxygen, produces light. Many organisms also produce the catalyst luciferase, which helps to speed up the reaction.

📽 @louiscole
📍 Venice Beach, California, USA
